## INSTRUCTIONS FOR AI ASSISTANTS\
\
When asked to create a new course page:\
\
1. **Start with the complete HTML template** (provided at top of this guide)\
\
2. **Identify the content type:**\
   - Simple content page? \uc0\u8594  Pattern 1\
   - Card-based layout? \uc0\u8594  Pattern 2\
   - Video collection? \uc0\u8594  Pattern 3\
   - Week-by-week outline? \uc0\u8594  Use week-card components\
   - Timeline? \uc0\u8594  Use timeline components\
\
3. **Build the structure:**\
   - Always include: AI notice, header, content wrapper\
   - Choose appropriate components from library\
   - Maintain spacing and padding consistency\
\
4. **Apply UCT colors:**\
   - Primary: #003A70\
   - Secondary: #2a5298\
   - Backgrounds: #f9f9f9, #f8f9fa\
   - Never use gradients or purple\
\
5. **Add polish:**\
   - Rounded corners on all containers\
   - Appropriate shadows\
   - Hover effects on interactive elements\
   - Emojis in titles/sections\
\
6. **Ensure responsiveness:**\
   - Include mobile breakpoint (@media max-width: 768px)\
   - Stack cards on mobile\
   - Reduce padding on small screens\
\
7. **Test checklist:**\
   - \uc0\u9989  All colors from UCT palette\
   - \uc0\u9989  Rounded corners on containers\
   - \uc0\u9989  Shadows on main container and cards\
   - \uc0\u9989  Proper spacing/padding\
   - \uc0\u9989  Hover effects work\
   - \uc0\u9989  Mobile responsive\
   - \uc0\u9989  Semantic HTML structure\
\
